2.5 km (by road) W of railroad and 3.5 km (by road) W of the Santa Cruz-Abapó highway and San Joaquín, along gravel road to Pozo PCH X1001, the turnoff 5.5 km S of Basilio. Chaco forest on gentle slopes on unconsolidated sediments, the easternmost Andean hills before the plains. With Anadenanthera macrocarpa, Herreria montevidensis, Trichilia claussenii, Ceiba speciosa, C. insignis, Bougainvillea stipitata, Pogonopus tubulosus and the columnar cacti Cereus dayami and C. comarapanus. Many Bignoniaceae vines (e.g.Perianthomega vellozii, Tynanthus polyanthus) with green fruit, buy only one blooming, no. 53132 Parabignonia chodatii. Many of the vines and shrubs appear to already be water-stressed. In partial shade.
